text:
Moien Abela, yesefere lij, welcome to beautiful Luxembourg. i would have been honered to host you had i known you were visiting our little beautiful Lux. i hope you enjoyed your stay to the fullest. 
You have discribed everything so accurately. But bear in mind that nothing in this world comes for "free". All the amazing things you saw including the free transport is made possible by tax payers money. Residents may pay upto 42%(the 0-42 % depending on the amount of income ofcourse) of their gross annual income for tax and on top of that extra for social security service(11% if they are employed or 25% if they are independent). So all the good things come with a price and that's why most people prefer a better work-life balance by working less hours than engaging in multiple jobs coz you'r gonna lose most of it on tax anyway and it's not worth it. 
That being said, The Shengen village, the casemate near the golden lady and the old steel factory in the south would have been very interesting to visit too. May be next time👌
Merci pour ta visite cher Abel et à très bientôt.😉
Love from Luxembourg.
